.TH MALUDB_MC2DBD 8 "2026-05-12" "maludb_mc2dbd 0.4.0" "MaluDB"
.SH NAME
maludb_mc2dbd \- MaluDB MC2DB listener (MCP-over-HTTPS sidecar)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maludb_mc2dbd
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B maludb_mc2dbd
exposes the MaluDB MC2DB tool registry as an MCP-compatible HTTP/HTTPS
endpoint. It connects to a PostgreSQL cluster running the
.B maludb_core
extension and dispatches MCP
.I tools/call
requests via one of four implementation_type backends:
.TP
.B sql_function
libpq into the PostgreSQL session (read or read-write per tool catalog).
.TP
.B external_exec
fork+exec a registered command with per-tool timeout, scrubbed env, and
absolute-path-only enforcement.
.TP
.B mcp_proxy
forwards
.I tools/call
to a remote MCP server over HTTP or stdio transport.
.TP
.B http_endpoint
generic REST-call dispatcher (POST/PUT/PATCH bodies from arguments
JSON, GET/DELETE bodyless), with optional bearer or basic auth.
.PP
The listener also exposes a Prometheus-compatible
.B /metrics
endpoint and a
.B /healthz
liveness probe.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Bind host. Default
.IR 127.0.0.1 .
.TP
.BR \-\-port " " \fIPORT\fR
Bind port. Default
.IR 5329 .
.TP
.BR \-\-pg-conninfo " " \fISTRING\fR
libpq connection string. Falls back to the standard
.BR PGHOST ", " PGDATABASE ", " PGUSER
environment variables if unset.
.TP
.B \-\-tls
Enable TLS on the listener. Requires
.B \-\-tls-cert
and
.BR \-\-tls-key .
.TP
.BR \-\-tls-cert " " \fIPATH\fR
TLS certificate file (PEM).
.TP
.BR \-\-tls-key " " \fIPATH\fR
TLS private key file (PEM).
.TP
.BR \-\-bearer-token " " \fITOKEN\fR
Require
.I Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>
on every request. May also be set via the
.B MALUDB_MC2DBD_TOKEN
environment variable.
.TP
.B \-\-foreground
Run in the foreground (do not daemonize). This is the default mode
used by the
.B maludb-mc2dbd.service
systemd unit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print usage and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/maludb/maludb-mc2dbd.conf
Default configuration file, read by the systemd unit. Defines
.BR HOST ", " PORT ", " PG_CONNINFO ", " MALUDB_MC2DBD_TOKEN .
.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/maludb-mc2dbd.service
Hardened systemd unit (ProtectSystem=strict, RestrictAddressFamilies,
etc.).
.TP
.I /etc/maludb/tls/server.crt
.TQ
.I /etc/maludb/tls/server.key
Optional TLS material referenced by
.BR \-\-tls-cert " and " \-\-tls-key .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MALUDB_MC2DBD_TOKEN
Bearer token required on every request (alternative to
.BR \-\-bearer-token ).
.TP
.BR PGHOST ", " PGDATABASE ", " PGUSER ", " PGPASSWORD
Standard libpq fallbacks when
.B \-\-pg-conninfo
is not set.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal shutdown.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command-line arguments.
.TP
.B 3
Configuration error (missing required option, malformed conninfo).
.TP
.B 4
Could not bind the listener socket or initialize libmicrohttpd.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR psql (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
.PP
See
.I /usr/share/doc/maludb-mc2dbd/README.Debian
for post-install configuration steps, and
.I /usr/share/maludb/scripts/maludb-validate
for a post-install sanity check.
